{"key":"post-17203602","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>17203602</id>\n<content>It's hard to get a lot of mycology supplies at regular stores because the demand is too low for them to stock the stuff.&amp;nbsp; You can get agar-agar at health and asian food markets.&amp;nbsp; You can get malt extract at health food or beer brewing shops. Blend the agar-agar into a flour with a coffee grinder and then boil to mix and dissolve the agar and malt.&amp;nbsp; Pour into a flask and sterilize as shown in the &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.mushroomvideos.com/Agar-Petri-Dishes&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noreferrer noopener&quot;&gt;agar/petri dishes video&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>17203742</next>\n<prev>17203595</prev>\n<first>17203206</first>\n<last>17204586</last>\n<when>1352691692</when>\n<utime>11/12/12 05:41 AM</utime>\n</post>"}